column2: Complete overcast- 10 mph wind- final reading of the year.
Exceptionally heavy rain 48 hours prior to reading.
Strong n-northwest winds for 3 days prior to reading.
High winds and heavy rains two days before.
Heavy boating activity for previous 3 days.
Light overcast- lake choppy- heavy activity since the 4th.
Light rain in A.M.- hazy afternoon- several water skiers.
Partly cloudy- light S breeze- no boats.
Sunny- S wind- surface getting rough.
Mostly sunny- calm- .4" rain early A.M.
Mostly sunny- strong NW wind- .6" rain last night.
Rained .2" 6/11- level higher than last year.
Cloudy- .3" rain on 7/4- heavy boat traffic.  Lake level: Rising
Clear- no rain for several days- W wind.
Light overcast- light chop- W breeze.
Sunny- calm- .5" rain Sun P.M.-.4" early Thurs-.1" Thursday evening.
Beautiful sunshine- air temperature is 65 degrees- calm - lake surface is almost a mirror.  Rain gauge reading from 8/2-8/3 is 0.7 inches.
Mostly cloudy- some sun- light rain.
Mostly sunny- variable breeze- no rain for several days.
Partly sunny- calm- 64 degrees.  Rain gauge reading from 7/9/-7/13 is 1.55 inches with 0.15" on 7/9- 0.60" on 7/10- 0.10" on 7/11- 0.60" on 7/12- and 0.10" on 7/13.

Overcast day- light southerly breeze- a few sprinkles.  Rain gauge reading from 7/15-8/6 is 1.85 inches with 0.1" from 7/15-7/16- 0.15" from 7/16-7/17- 0.7" from 7/19-7/20- 0.12" from 7/21-7/22- and 0.2" from 7/31-8/1.

Overcast- light variable breeze- 58 degrees.  Rain gauge reading from 8/7-8/29 is 2.49 inches.  8/7-8/8 was 0.65"- 8/10-8/11 was 0.09"- 8/12-8/18 was 0.60"- 8/25-8/26 was 1"- and on 8/27-8/28 there was 0.15".
Cloudy- 52 degrees- light mist or fog descending across the lake.
Partly sunny- 58 degrees- light southwest breeze.
A clear sunny day- 55 degrees- very light southwesterly breeze- saw my first large flight of Canadian geese!
Partly sunny- air temp 60- light NW breeze.
Sunny- calm- air temp 71- surface water temp 66- 2" of rain 6/7-6/8.
Sunny- 76 F- Pudge Edinger helped "on lake" part. rainfall 7/1-7/5 .6"- light S breeze.
Sunny- air temp 65- light north-northeast breeze- .3" rain 7/19.
Mostly sunny- few clouds- air temp 66- strong NE breeze- rain: .6" 7/25- .3" 7/28.
Mostly sunny- 63 degrees- north to northwest breeze.
Light west-southwest breeze- air temp 72- partly sunny- no measurable precipitation.
Partly cloudy- 55 degrees- light southwest breeze.
At 10:15 we clouded over so both readings were under cloud cover.  78 degrees-light SW breeze.
Secchi level at site 1 was 10.5 ft.  Partly cloudy- south breeze- 76 degrees- boat traffic is increasing.  I had a jet ski and 2 boats pulling skiers plus 3 boats with fishermen.
Northeast breeze- 68 degrees- partly sunny- had the entire lake to my self.  Not even a fishermen!  Lake surface a little choppy.
Surface choppy-72 degrees.  Deep hole 50' of water.  15.5' near shore-about 20' of water.  Tried nearer shore- but secchi hit bottom and was very visible.
Cloudy-feels like rain-66 degrees.  7/31/94 received 0.70" of rain.
Partly sunny- 62 degrees- southerly breeze.  8/8 0.3" of rain- 8/10 0.1" of rain.
Cloudy- had rained earlier this morning- 60 degrees.  8/18 1.85" of rain- 8/19 0.20- 8/20 0.20.
Partly sunny- a very calm day- the lake surface with hardly a ripple.
Lots of rain- water is warmer then average- weather just turned colder.
72 degrees- westerly breeze.  Lake almost calm.  Three boats with fishermen.
A beautiful morning- very soft southerly breeze- lake surface almost a mirror- saw only one other boat- sunny and 68 degrees.
.65" rain 9/6/95- 34 degrees F at 7:00 a.m. today.  Bright and sunny with slight west winds after 2 days of north winds.
65 degrees.  Partly cloudy- cumulus.  E winds -pine pollen floating.
Bright sunny morning-72 degrees-soft NW breeze. 6/12 1.25" of rain- 6/6 0.5"- 6/17 0.6"- 6/10 0.5".
Sunny day-76 degrees-southwest breeze. 6/17 1.05"- 6/18 0.95"- 6/19 0.55" of rain. what a nice lake day.
Mostly sunny- 66 degrees- SW breeze- a few fisherman to keep us company- two boats pulling little ones in rubber raft.
Sunny day-64 degrees-north breeze. lake has a slight chop. 6/27 0.6"- 7/2 1.0" of rainfall.
Partly sunny-70 degrees-lake nearly calm-a few fisherman-7/6 0.15" of rain last night.
Sunny-67 degrees-strong southerly breeze. 7/18 received 1.2" of rain. too much wind for many sailors-the sunfish would really fly.
68 degrees-sunny-calm. 8/13 to 8/14 could be called "car spotters"-very brief showers.
68 degrees-sunny-southwest wind-light chop on the lake-8/19 0.55"- 8/22 0.225" rainfall.  PWC are a weekend nuisance!
Beautiful fall day- windy- chop on water- 50 degrees.  Few boats.  Difficult to get reading.
Nice day to be on the lake-mild- sun- slight breeze-no boats.  End of '96 testing.
Have had very frequent and high winds.  Rain gauge reading 5/24/97 to 5/31/97=0.75 inches.
Nice day but too windy.  Rain gauge reading from 6/1 to 6/25=2.65 inches.
Calm- few boats.  Loons and ducks.  Rain gauge reading from 7/29 to 8/25=2.75 inches.
Four loons on lake- two adults and two babies.  Beautiful color starting.  Slight breeze- very sunny.  60 degrees.  Rain gauge reading from 8/25 to 9/26=2.25 inches.
Gorgeous morning- dead calm- no boats.
Clear- sunny- cold- and saw three loons on the lake.
Overcast- very warm- and saw seven loons on the lake.
Sunny- warm- and saw an eagle but no loons.
Overcast- warm- and saw an eagle and two loons.
Raw day- cloudy- slight chop. Saw loons
Beautiful- calm sunny day. Loons with 2 babies on back.
Beautiful- calm- sunny. Loons with 2 young - East and West Lake
Beautiful- calm- sunny. Saw 1 loon East lake
Cool. Sunny- slight chop. One loon East lake. Much rain.
Sunny- lite ripple.  No loons or fishermen.  1 eagle.
EAST-SITE 2 - DEEP HOLE - VERTICAL WATER SAMPLER
sunny- clear- breezy sighted two loons
sunny- windy- sighted gulls and loons water rough
sunny following rain- slight breeze lot of debris on lake- wind came up
Partly cloudy- little chop wind picked up from the w/sw
Sunny- light breeze fron the west
Partly sunny- very windy on 6/1/2011 gusts up to 60mph
Mostly sunny- light west breeze 5-10 mph
Mostly sunny- light W/NW breeze- 18 hrs prior to sampling thunderstorm went through with brief high winds(estimated 50mph)
Mostly Cloudy- warm- humid- 1.5" rain 36hrs. ago
Partly Cloudy- hot and humid- wind west 5mph- 4" rain in past week.
Cloudy with light sprinkles and calm winds.
Partly sunny- air temp. 42 degrees and light breeze from east.
Cloudy with 10mph winds from the south.
Mostly clear- light west breeze- pine tree pollen in water.
Sunny- light breeze- 1.5" rain last night.
Mostly cloudy- wind NNE 10MPH- ice out 5/05/2018.
Mostly cloudy- wind light from N.
Sunny- Wind W5- 3" of rain yesterday.
